data.text:
This is a timeline of galactic history—a chronological record of events relevant to the galaxy. This timeline uses dates in terms of years before the Battle of Yavin (BBY) and after the Battle of Yavin (ABY).

This in-universe list is incomplete. You can help Wookieepedia by expanding it.

Timeline of galactic history[]

Before the Republic (eons–25,025 BBY)[]

Sentient species prehistory

The universe begins forming.[2]

The galaxy is formed around a super-massive black hole.[3]

Midi-chlorians are birthed from the Wellspring of Life. They are microscopic symbiotic organisms in all living things that connect the Living Force—the energy of all life—to the Cosmic Force, allowing the will of the all-encompassing energy field known as the Force to communicate with lifeforms.[4]

The Father, the Son, and the Daughter exist as powerful Force wielders who come to live in the ethereal realm of Mortis.[5]

Billions of years before the Imperial Era, mineral matter that would infuse rock walls on the planet Ilum with valuable constituents, including rare crystals such as the Force-attuned kyber, begin to accumulate.[6]

The long lived Exogorth species comes into existance. Over one billion years before the Imperial Era, the Exogorth Sy-O is born to Sy-O's father-and-mother. However, at even one billion, Sy-O would be considered young by Exogorth standards.[7]

Billions to millions of years before the Imperial Era, lava flows on Dagobah and form Mount Dagger before disappearing to allow for the flourishing of non-sentient life.[8]

A non-sentient species lives on the world of Bravais, eventually evolving into the sentient Bravaisian.[9]

A non-sentient species lives on the planet Crul millions of years before they evolve into the sentient Crolute.[9]

A primitive species lives on the planet Abednedo, eventually evolving into the sentient Abednedo.[9]

Sentient species history (exact chronology undefined)

In ancient times, beings from a distant galaxy built a reflex point on the planet Seatos which pointed the way to the extragalactic planet Peridea.[10] The people become known as the Dathomiri.[11]

A star map pointing the way to Peridea's galaxy was also stored inside a former Nightsister stronghold on Arcana.[12]

100,000 BBY

Beginning of the construction of the first city levels of Coruscant in the Core Worlds.[13]

57,000 BBY

Utapau is settled[14] by colonists who eventually evolve into the Pau'an and Utai species.[15]

Pre-hyperspace travel

Batuu, a planet on the edge of the Outer Rim Territories, is colonized millennia after a great cataclysm resulted in the planet's giant trees being destroyed and eventually petrified.[16]

A sentient ancestral species[17] invents the hyperdrive after studying the hyperspace-traveling purrgil,[18] opening up the galaxy for exploration.[17]

Post-hyperspace travel

c. 30,000 BBY

Devaronians, naturally adept as scouts, become active as galactic explorers from their native planet Devaron, independently developing the hyperdrive.[8]

The Outer Rim planet Benetage is abandoned.[8]

c. 27,000 BBY

Felucia is colonized by Gossam Courivers[19]

By this point, human civilization had developed on Empress Teta in the Deep Core.[8]

The Old Republic (c. 25,025 – c. 1000 BBY)[]

Dawn of the Jedi (c. 25,025 BBY)[]

c. 25,025 BBY

The Dai Bendu, the religious group that would be attributed with the first holocrons, exists as the precursor to the Jedi Order.[20]

In pursuit of the preservation of peace and justice, an individual who came to be known as the Prime Jedi founds the Jedi Order on Ahch-To.[21][22]

The First Jedi Temple is built on Ahch-To,[21] and the Jedi village is constructed on the Temple Island soon afterward.[22]

Shortly after the founding of the Jedi Order, the world Ilum is discovered by a Jedi scout through Force-assisted hyperspace navigation.[8]

c. 25,020 BBY

Professor Huyang powers up.[21]

c. 25,000 BBY

The Galactic Republic is formed[21][23] by the Core Founders, twenty-two Core Worlds which include such planets as Alderaan.[24]

Expansionist Period (25,000 BBY)[]

25,000 BBY (continued)

Expansionist Period

The foundation of the Corellian Run helps the formation of the Corellia system. The Corellian Trade Spine and the Perlemian Trade Route are also founded.[25]

Duros explorers discover and colonize the planet Neimoidia.[26]

The planet Cato Neimoidia joins the Republic.[27]

Millennia before the Imperial Era[]

Eons before the Imperial Era (exact chronology undefined)

The comet Kinro is predicted to carve its way through the Core Worlds. Before it can enter the Mid Rim, members of the Jedi Order come together and will it apart, although several Jedi lose their lives or minds in the process.[28]

By this point, the ice moon Mesula had been shattered.[29]

The first Grand Zigoth of Utapau, Krynbalt Kyr, dies.[29]

Thousands of years before the Clone Wars or the Imperial Era (exact chronology undefined)

The Predori empire opposed the Galactic Republic.[30]

A sentient species constructs a wormhole gate that leads between the seams of time and space, facilitating their exodus from the wider galaxy.[31]

The Temple of the Kyber is constructed on the cold, desert moon of Jedha.[32]

Hylemane Lightbringer is born and later bludgeoned to death by a chair, disproving the myth that "he could not be killed by mortal weapons."[28]

The Zygerrian Slave Empire is defeated by Jedi Knights.[33]

A rogue Jedi[34] leads a group of Force users to seek greater power through embracing the dark side of the Force. They split from the Jedi Order[17] during the schism known as the Hundred-Year Darkness,[35] becoming the rivaling Sith. Defeated, they are exiled by the Jedi Order, which serves the light side of the Force, and flee from known space to Korriban, a world of red sands that was later known as Moraband.[34]

Unbeknownst to others, the Sith on Korriban rebuild and prepare their revenge,[34] erecting massive Sith temples and tombs in the Valley of the Dark Lords.[36]

Over time, the Sith Empire, with the use of enslaved beings,[37] vies for control of the galaxy. They build gargantuan superweapons powered by kyber crystals to battle the Jedi.[38][39]

The carbonite mines of the Empress Teta system are conquered by the Krath.[40]

22,000–5000 BBY[]

22,000 BBY

The planet Neimoidia joins the Galactic Republic as an independent world in itself.[26]

c. 21,032 BBY[41]

The Blood Monarchy is established on Thisspias, the site of many battles during the Great Manifest Period.[20]

c. 20,000 BBY

An attack on Garn, later known as the Doom of the Ordu Aspectu, occurs—the Fortress of Garn was possessed by the Ordu Aspectu, a splinter group of the Jedi Order. Led by Rur[42] and related to the Massassi,[43] their experiments on immortality led to conflicts with Jedi orthodoxy, beginning the Entruvia Conflict. A dating system based on the signing of the Domancion Accord was used around this time,[44] and the conflict ended with a Jedi—Ordu Aspectu peace treaty: Jedi inspectors arrived at Rur's citadel, and, believing they intended to deactivate him, an artificial intelligence made of Rur's knowledge seized control of the citadel's droids and slaughtered its inhabitants. Rur sacrificed himself to deactivate the machine, hyperspace-jumping the citadel across the galaxy.[42]

15,000 BBY

Rodia officially joins the Galactic Republic.[45]

The physical distinctions between the Neimoidian and Duros species becomes clear on Neimoidia.[26]

12,000 BBY

Settlers from Corellia colonize a planet that becomes an Ordance/Regional Depot known as Ord Mantell.[46]

As credited by the Jedi, the planet Ossus comes to be their cultural center, and is made a near-mandatory pilgrimage site.[47]

7977 BBY

The Coruscant reckoning calendar is introduced.[40]

c. 6000 BBY

Civilization on Bardotta begins, with the Frangawl Cult reigning over a militant society.[8]

5500 BBY

The Rimma Trade Route is established.[25]

c. 5100 BBY

The Chiss Ascendancy is formed.[21]

5019 BBY

The Chiss start exploring the Unknown Regions.[21]

Wars of the Old Republic (c. 5000 – c. 1000 BBY)[]

Battles with the Jedi (c. 5000 BBY)[]

c. 5000 BBY

Soon after Empress Teta's Unification Wars,[8] the Great Hyperspace War is waged by the Sith Lord Naga Sadow according to the Qel-Droma Epics.

The Sith wage a war against the Jedi and[15] the Galactic Republic,[23] which sees the fall of the Republic capital and cityworld Coruscant.[15] This allows the Sith to build a shrine on the planet which exudes the force of the dark side. However, the Jedi eventually repel the Sith and reclaim Coruscant.[17]

According to the Qel-Droma Epics, the Great Jedi Library on Ossus is established as the physical embodiment of Jedi knowledge.[49] The library's construction was said to be overseen by the Odan-Urr,[8] a Jedi Master who annotated on a "Phases of Mortis" solution to the Unsolved Theorem of Master Thorpe, which was inscribed on a book dating to millennia BBY.[50]

The original Rammahgon was thought to have been destroyed at around this point.[51]

The Great Temple is built by the Massassi on Yavin 4.[52][53]

The Chiss obtain the alien Starflash superweapon.[21]

c. 5000 – c. 1000 BBY[]

c. 4300 BBY[21]

A war occurs between the Chiss Ascendancy and a Chiss enemy. The war ends with the Final Assault on Csilla, where the Starflash is used. The Ascendancy wins the war, but the star flash damages the output of Csilla's sun.[54]

c. 4260 BBY

The Chiss begin a clandestine exodus from Csilla to colony worlds.[21]

Almost a century before c. 4000 BBY

Human explorers from Grizmallt in the Core discover a Mid Rim world they name Nabu, later known as Naboo. The native Gungans retreat into their swamps and lakes.[8]

c. 4000 BBY

Fleeing civil war on Grizmallt, human refugees make Nabu their new home, discovering the presence of Gungans while settling in. The humans and the Gungans make war against each other in the next few decades before agreeing to live separately. Gungan society had flourished on the world in the preceding millennia after the sudden departure of the Elders, a reptilian sentient civilization that colonized Nabu and waged war against the indigenes. Before the Elders' arrival, the Gungans had lived on Nabu in large nomadic tribes for millennia.[8]

Later, the Gungan tribes are united under Boss Gallo and commence the building of Otoh Gunga as their capital city. Meanwhile, the humans, calling themselves "the Naboo," split into warring factions; the Time of Suffering is begun.[8]

According to the Qel-Droma Epics, the Crusade of Krath occurs in which thousands of Jedi are felled by a new Sith Empire until the redemption of Ulic Qel-Droma.[8]

According to the Qel-Droma Epics, Ossus is devastated by the Cron Supernovae, which were triggered by Naga Sadow.[8]

c. 3966 BBY

By this point, galactic travelers navigate hyperspace using hyperspace sextants.[55]

Sith accounts describing the kyber weaponry built by Darth Tanis[50] within the Sith temple on Malachor[56] are made.[57]

Eventually, a cataclysmic event[58] at the Battle of Malachor,[59] later known in legends as the "Great Scourge of Malachor,"[58] occurs during the era of great conflict that began around 5000 BBY;[59] Jedi Knights of the Old Republic era[58] uncover the battle station and confront the Sith. All participants are petrified by the superweapon,[56] including a witch who led the Sith forces,[60] although an entity known as the Presence remained in a Sith holocron within the Malachor temple.[56] Afterwards, Jedi are forbidden from traveling to Malachor, and data on the location is removed from the Jedi Archives.[58]

By the time of the Great Scourge, the crossguard lightsaber design has become common among Makashi practitioners.[61]

c. 3700 BBY

Ord Mantell becomes a trading post for spacers.[46]

c. 3650 BBY

The Chiss are involved in wars of the Old Republic.[21]

c. 3450 BBY

The Chiss withdraw from the wider galaxy.[21]

3277 BBY

The Lothal Calendar is introduced.[62]

c. 2500 BBY

The Drengir ally themselves with the Sith. However, the latter capture the Great Progenitor on Amaxine Space Station and the Drengir fall into a state of dormancy.[21]

2320 BBY

Taanab is colonized by settlers who introduce transplanted farmstock to the world, transforming it into an agricultural outpost.[63]

Over 2019 BBY; millennia before 19 BBY (exact chronology undefined)[64]

The Force vergence Acablas on Auratera comes to be a known destination for Jedi Masters and Sith Lords, with Auratera aligning itself with the Galactic Republic or whichever Sith Empire that controlled the surrounding star systems.[8]

Bardotta's Jour-un becomes a trading hub and the planet's major spaceport.[8]

The Cron Drift asteroid field is established in the Auril sector, preventing expeditions to the ancient Jedi world of Ossus.[8]

Iktotch is incorporated into the Galactic Republic.[8]

Weik is colonized by sentients.[8]

Between 2022 and 2019 BBY

The Klorri-clan battle shield is introduced. The Wookiees of Kashyyyk would reserve the battle shield for use in important rituals and ceremonies.[66]

c. 2000 BBY

Boothi XII is settled by farmers[67] who lead simple lives and whose architecture of sheds would outlast the Republic's existence.[68]

The Jedi code used by the Force wielders on Mortis to draw in Anakin Skywalker, Obi-Wan Kenobi, and Ahsoka Tano during the Clone Wars is last used around this time.[69]

The Dagoyan Order takes hold of Bardotta after a series of successful and strategic small-scale wars; the once ruling Frangawl Cult goes into hiding.[8]

The Arakein Monks set in stone a clock atop Mount Arakeirkos. According to legend, whoever watches each swing of its pendulum for a day will have the lifespan of the universe revealed before their eyes.[70]

c. 1300 BBY[21]

Following the B'ankora homeworld cataclysm, Republic Chancellor Chasen Piian grants the B'ankora survivors sanctuary on Coruscant.[71]

c. 1100 – 1000 BBY

Momin is trained by Lady Shaa.[21] Eventually, Momin kills his Master and travels the galaxy honing his craft. Later, he and his acolytes are slain by a pair of Jedi during his destruction of a city through the use of a superweapon, although Lord Momin's spirit survives through his mask. His story is deemed heretical by the Sith and is suppressed.[72]

c. 1050 BBY

The first Mandalorian Jedi, Tarre Vizsla, creates the Darksaber.[21]

The fall of the Old Republic[73]

The Mandalorians had been waging war against the Jedi[74] and against the Republic,[75] during which the Mandalorian crusades,[74] the devastation of Ubduria,[9] and, in the final stages, the cataclysm that reduced Mandalore to a wasteland occurred.[76]

By the time of the Sith's defeat (exact chronology undefined)

Before the time of the Galactic Republic, the lushly forested planet Mustafar was inhabited by off-worlder Lady Corvax, who lived in harmony with the native Mustafarians along with her husband. The latter died as a result of an attack on Mustafar, leading to Corvax's theft of the most sacred Mustafarian relic, the Bright Star, in an attempt to use it in a ritual to resurrect her love.[77] The ritual failed; instead, the Bright Star's energies pushed Mustafar into a new orbit, reducing the world to an unbalanced, chaotic state. A volcanic wasteland is created[77] as tiny Mustafar is torn between gas giants Lefrani and Jestefad.[15] Thus, Sith seeking the secrets of eternal life were attracted to the world.[50]

Radaki[78] had left the Jedi Order, believing that Jedi should retain their family ties and wealth. Thus he was seduced by the dark side of the force, becoming the Sith Lord Darth Krall.[79]

Sith victory at the Battle of Wasted Years; this would be attributed to Darth Krall, who would also be remembered for taming the Nightmare Conjunction and as one of the Lost Twenty.[79]

By this point, the Middle Era of the Old Republic has occurred.[73] Bith operas existed at that time.[80]

c. 1032 BBY

The Four Masters[15] construct the Jedi Temple[21] atop the ruins of the Sith shrine on Coruscant in an attempt to contain and eliminate its power,[17] as well as to take advantage of the area's strength in the Force.[15]

Defeat of the Sith (1032 BBY)[]

1032 BBY[21]

The Jedi-Sith War[81] ends with the Jedi Order and Republic forces victorious.[73]

Coruscant and the Jedi Temple had been occupied by the Sith as part of the war[73] and the Darksaber stolen from the temple by Mandalorians.[74]

By this point, Coruscant and the Jedi Temple are liberated by Jedi and Republic forces.[73]

The Brotherhood of Darkness,[82] an army of the Sith in which Darth Bane served,[83] are defeated by the Jedi's Army of Light[82] as a result of infighting amongst themselves.[84] The Sith, who once numbered thousands,[85] are driven into hiding[17] and are eventually thought extinct.[86]

The sole Sith survivor, Darth Bane,[87] creates the Grand Plan—a plot to destroy the Jedi and the Republic from within for the coming of Sith rule over the galaxy[88]—and establishes the[89] Rule of Two,[36] a lineage of Sith who would operate in the shadows, preserving the Sith's vendetta against the Jedi whilst preparing for their own return. Centuries before the Clone Wars, the Rule of Two is revealed to the Jedi Order, though still they presume the Sith's eradication and believe that Bane's plan is ruined with his defeat[89] allegedly at the hands of his apprentice, Darth Zannah, in a duel on the Inner Rim planet Ambria. This pattern is repeated by nearly all Sith thereafter.[90]

The Sith Lord becomes the last of his kind to be laid to rest on Moraband's Valley of the Dark Lords.[89]

The Sith Wars waged between the Republic and the Sith Empire[91] has ended by this point. The Sith Wars saw the participation of the Jedi Order on the side of the Republic[8] as well as the participation of the Chiss Ascendancy, which encountered multiple alien species before retreating to their borders.[91] The Jedi Cervil the Uncanny had left begind testimonies about lightwhips being effective against the Sith's Forbidden Forms,[93] and Ithorian population of Auratera continues restoring the world to its natural state following the Sith Wars.[8]

c. 1022 BBY

The Amaxine warriors disappear from the known galaxy.[21]

c. 1000 BBY

The Massassi become extinct.[21]

The translation of Sith runes is outlawed.[21]

In the aftermath of the Corsair Wars, Master Oo'ob breaks with Jedi doctrine, pursuing a pre-emptive method of dealing with threats to galactic peace. He and his partner, noted crystallist Var-Whill, develop the Farkiller, and use it to kill a number of "emergent" despots. Within the decade, the Jedi Council pronounces them apostate and eventually purges them,[94] with Oo'ob's expulsion taking place around 1000 BBY.[21]

Republic Era (c. 1000 – 19 BBY)[]

Reformation of the Republic (c. 1000 BBY)[]

c. 1000 BBY (continued)

Founding of the modern Galactic Republic; with the Republic's definitive victory, its capital resettles on Coruscant, and the time before this rebirth is forgotten as a dark age, the "Old Republic." Official calendars begin anew,[73] and the Old Republic military is disbanded.[17] By this point,[95] the Galactic Senate, newly founded by several star systems,[96] elects Tarsus Valorum[81] as the first Supreme Chancellor.[17]

Around this time, the Coruscant Jedi Temple begins serving as the Jedi Order's operational and spiritual headquarters.

The Yavin Code is established at the Yavin Convention.[98]

The Bardottan Royal Palace is constructed. (Approximate date)[99]

The construction of the Royal Palace of Alderaan begins.[100] After the initial buildingwork, additional chambers are added every few decades.[101]

What will be remembered as the most unpredictable and thrilling instance of the Dragon Void race until the race involving Han Solo occurs.[102]

The Anchorite sect, a light side group on Jakku believing that suffering was the basis of life, binds itself to the Jedi Order.[103]

Auratera is concealed from official charts and isolated from the galaxy at large by the Jedi and its populace to prevent future Sith or other dark side Force users from accessing the planet's Acablas vergence.[8]

c. 1014 BBY[104]

Ilum's Jedi Temple is built.[104]

c. 1000 – c. 500 BBY[]

c. 973 BBY

Maz Kanata is born.[105]

c. 972 BBY

Galactic Accord of Systems establishes rules for any future armed conflicts.[21]

c. 965 BBY

The Dai Bendu Monastery[106] is constructed on Mount Izukika of the planet Kijimi.[107]

900 BBY

Sky Three is first manufactured by North River Freight.

896 BBY

Yoda is born.[21]

c. 873 BBY

Maz Kanata settles on Takodana.[21]

867 BBY

Naboo joins the Galactic Republic.[21]

832 BBY[21]

General Jafan ends Naboo's longstanding Time of Suffering[8] and restores peace to the planet.[15]

Theed is founded, and the Theed Royal Palace is constructed in the same year under the direction of King Jafan. Uniter[8] and ruler of all the Naboo, Jafan becomes the first ruler of the Great Time of Peace.[15]

800 BBY

Kuat Drive Yards purchases the planet Rothana, eventually leading to the establishment of Rothana Heavy Engineering.[109]

796 BBY

Yoda begins to train Jedi in the ways of the Force.[21]

620 BBY

The Antarian Rangers are founded to assist the Jedi Order as a security force on Antar IV.[110]

600 BBY

Jabba Desilijic Tiure is born on Nal Hutta.[21]

c. 522 BBY

The Citadel is built on Lola Sayu to imprison rogue Jedi.

519 BBY

With the Kallidahin believing themselves to be descendants of the extinct Eellayin people, the Archaeological Research Council of Kallidah establishes a Research Base on one of the largest fragments of ancient Polis Massa, which was once home to the Eellayin and had suffered a planetary cataclysm long ago. Archaeologists begin to survey and excavate the entirety of the Polis Massa asteroid belt, seeking to discover more of their ancestors as well as other alien species with cloning skills learned from the Kaminoans.[15]

c. 511 BBY

The planet Jelucan is colonized by off-worlders exiled from another world for not breaking allegiance to their king.

c. 509 BBY

Yaddle is born.[114]

c. 500 BBY

The armor that will become Sabine Wren's is forged.[115]

High Republic Era (c. 500 – 100 BBY)[]

c. 500 BBY

The Everon Exodus occurs.[21]

By c. 483 BBY

The Path of the Open Hand is formed.[116]

c. 482 BBY

Jedi Barnabas Vim performs a mission to Angcord[117]

c. 407 BBY

The Ikkrukkian Porter Engle and the Kage Barash Silvain train as Jedi younglings.[119]

c. 400 BBY

Rumors persist of Planet X.[21]

Thomas Toov is born.[120]

c. 392 BBY

Republic and Jedi pathfinder teams start exploring the Outer Rim.[21]

c. 387 BBY

The Forever War between Eiram and E'ronoh begins.[21]

c. 383 BBY

The Great Hyperspace Rush occurs,[21] making hyperspace travel safer.[93]

382 BBY

By this point, the Convocation of the Force has been established on Jedha.[21]

The Rod of Seasons is stolen by the Children of the Open Hand.

Jedi Zallah Macri and Kevmo Zink investigate the Path of the Open Hand on Dalna in search of the Rod of Seasons.

The Ambush on Thelj occurs.

The Path of the Open Hand leaves Dalna for Jedha.

The Chancellors of the Republic negotiate a peace between Eiram and E'ronoh during a summit aboard the Paxion.[21]

The Wedding of Phan-tu Zenn and Xiri A'lbaran, the heirs of Eiram and E'ronoh respectively, occurs.[122]

Jedi Masters Porter Engle and Barash Silvain[119] undertake a mission on Gansevor.[21] Silvain blames herself for the losses at the siege there, led by General Abediah Viess, and vows to distance herself from the rest of the Jedi Order, including her brother, Engle. Engle later breaks the siege of Bardotta, earning the nickname "Blade of Bardotta."[123]

A summit is held on Jedha for the Eiram–E'ronoh peace treaty to be signed.[21]

The summit is bombed.[122]

The Temple of the Kyber is bombed.[122]

The Battle of Jedha occurs.[21]

The Path of the Open Hand retreats to Dalna, and some of its members undertake a mission to Planet X to retrieve the Nameless, a creature that fed on Force-sensitives.[124]

While the Jedi investigate the Path of the Open Hand on Dalna, they found the Path of the Closed Fist and attack the investigators.[124]

The Jedi defeat the Path on the Night of Sorrow.[21] Jedi Azlin Rell falls to the dark side after devoting his life to studying the Nameless after encountering them during the battle.[125]

The Path of the Open Hand is dissolved.[126]

Marda Ro founds what will become the Nihil pirate organization.[127]

350 BBY

The Trade Federation is founded by Neimoidians.[26]

c. 332 BBY

The Jafan family leads a people to colonize what became known as the planet Jafan in the Chommell sector. The planet is ruled by the Jafan family until at least 32 BBY.[128][129]

By this point, the mining industry on Elphrona,[130] a world located on the edge of the Unknown Regions in the Outer Rim,[131] is established.[130]

c. 319 BBY

The third volume of the Aionomica book is subject to a forgery scandal.[132]

Mustafar comes into the possession of the Techno Union.[133] The Union charges the native Mustafarians rent[50] whilst providing the technology for them to mine their mineral-rich world.[66] The natives' labor serves to pay their rent, and the planet becomes known for its mining activities.[50]

c. 318 BBY

The modern Chiss Syndicure is formed, ending an era where armed conflicts between rival Chiss families was common.[54]

c. 272 BBY

Invaders surface on Pamarthe for the last time until at least 28 ABY.[135]

Lourna Dee is born.[136]

c. 265 BBY

Faddaff Davenspon is born.[137]

c. 262 BBY

Avar Kriss is born.[138]

c. 257 BBY

The Jedi Order's T-1 shuttle sees action in[139] the Eiram–E'ronoh crisis.[140] Fillithar Jedi Master Simmix is killed in a ship crash, leaving his Padawan, Cohmac Vitus, conflicted over the Jedi ways of non-attachment. Vitus nevertheless resolved the crisis alongside Master Laret Soveral and her Padawan, the Umbaran Orla Jareni.[139]

c. 255 BBY

Lourna Dee is rescued by Oppo Rancisis and joins the Carida military academy.[21]

c. 252 BBY

Innamin is born.[141]

c. 250 BBY

By this point, Pra-Tre Veter had joined the Jedi High Council. While Veter is still a new member, Grandmaster Yoda responds to the raids on the Scalvi, teaching him patience and trust and inspiring the conflict between the Scalvi and the Crulkon to be resolved peacefully.[143]

Bell Zettifar is born.

Lourna Dee joins the Nihil.[21]

c. 249 BBY

Affie Hollow and Reath Silas are born.[145]

c. 248 BBY

Vernestra Rwoh is born.[146]

247 BBY

Bell Zettifar joins the Jedi Order.

Lourna Dee saves Asgar Ro from an assassination attempt and is promoted to Tempest Runner.[21]

c. 244 BBY

A largely isolated colony is established on Sedri Minor.[147]

Avon Sunvale is born.[148]

c. 242 BBY

Serj Ukkarian is born.[149]

c. 240 BBY

Dez Rydan passes the Jedi Trials and becomes a Jedi Knight.[150]

c. 234 BBY

Lina Soh is elected Supreme Chancellor of the Republic.[21]

c. 233 – 232 BBY[21]

Ady Sun'Zee overcomes her fear at the Batuu Jedi temple with the help of Grand Master Yoda.[151]

c. 232 BBY[21]

By this point, the Jedi had stopped a droid uprising on Kligson's Moon.[152]

A raid on Hap's Sap Tap takes place on Tenoo.[153]

The Kublop Springs festival occurs.[154]

The Skirmish in Kublop Springs marketplace occurs.[155]

The Kublop Classic occurs.[156]

The Search for the Star Seeker occurs.[157]

The Search for the Yara leaves occurs.[158]

A Wellagrin migration occurs on planet Andraven.[159]

The Jellyfruit Festival occurs.[160]

A Discovery of burrowberry bird occurs.[161]

The Test flight on Dedoon occurs.[162]

The Search for Figgles occurs.[163]

At this point, the Outer Rim contains few well-mapped hyperspace lanes that allows those seeking adventure, as well as those seeking to evade the Republic's laws, to do so.<[164]

The Coruscant-based Republic Chancellor Lina Soh envisions a galaxy of Great Works that ranged from infrastructure to culture in an effort to expand the Republic's reaches, better connect the peoples of the galaxy, and bring inspiration and peace for all citizens. Efforts are made to negotiate a new peace treaty between the Quarren and the Mon Calamari, as well as to mass-produce bacta—a "miracle" substance[164] primarily made from a barley originally cultivated on Thyferra[165] that was intended to replace juvan—in the hopes of revolutionizing medicine.[164]

As part of Chancellor Soh's pledge to maintain the Republic's hold on[164] the hard-to-navigate Outer Rim,[166] outreach programs are established in the Rim.[164]

In the Galactic Frontier,[21] the Jedi maintain order and justice at independently operated outposts, working closely with the Republic without direct assistance from the Coruscant Jedi Temple.[164]

In hyperspace, the Legacy Run, a Kaniff Yards Class A modular freight transport of the Byne Guild, encounters a Nihil ship and is destroyed.[164] The Byne Guild's Kezarat Convoy disappears on the same day.[167] Starships across the galaxy are abruptly knocked out of hyperspace by missiles of debris from the Legacy Run, which also threaten to destroy space stations, moons, as well as planets.
